      <abstract id="4e5b8cad-5b5c-40d0-9265-f0063ee1452c">
        <label>Abstract</label>
        <p>A new species of <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Orthosiphon</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> (<tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="family">Lamiaceae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>), <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Orthosiphon</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">cinereus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> A.J.Paton, sp. nov. from Angola is described and the eight species of <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Orthosiphon</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> in Angola listed with reference to previous accounts. <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Orthosiphon</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">newtonii</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Briq. is reduced to the synonymy of <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Endostemon</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">tubulascens</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> (Briq.) M.Ashby.</p>
